# ==============================================================================
# COMPLETE PIPELINE: Load 52 Visium Samples → Identify Niche Cells
# Spatially Proximal to ASPC → L-R Analysis from Gene Readout in
# Niche Cells to Gene Readout in ASPC
# in NEPC vs Adenocarcinoma
#
# KEY DESIGN:
#   - NO hardcoded ASPC_receptors list
#   - Ligands retrieved from CellChat L-R database, measured in niche CT spots
#   - Receptors retrieved from CellChat L-R database, measured in ASPC spots
#   - Both sides are pure gene readout from Visium data
#   - CellChat defines WHICH genes are ligands and WHICH are receptors
#   - Visium defines HOW MUCH each gene is expressed WHERE
#   - SUPPLEMENTED with curated Nerve-specific L-R pairs not in CellChat
#   - NEPC classification: NEPC spots (NE_like_hi) > 5% total spots
#   - CONTROLS:
#       Control 1: Background-corrected niche enrichment
#                  (ASPC-niche minus global sample average)
#       Control 2: Random-spot permutation
#                  (niche around random spots vs ASPC spots, 100 permutations)
#
# v2 — Absolute NE_like threshold calibrated from known NEPC (NEADT) samples
#       to eliminate BPH false positives. Per-sample quantile thresholds are
#       retained for all OTHER cell types (niche composition analysis).
#
# L-R DATABASE: CellChat (CellChatDB) + Curated Nerve→Stroma supplement
# SAMPLES: 4 BPH + 17 TRNA + 22 NEADT + 5 CRPC + 4 MET = 52
# ==============================================================================

